article.headline: Youngstown St. 73, Toledo 67
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio -- Vytas Sulskis scored 20 points and Damian Eargle added 15 to lead Youngstown State over Toledo 73-67 on Wednesday night. Sulskis made four of the Penguins' (3-1) 11 3-pointers and Eargle had six of their 10 blocks in keeping the Rockets (0-6) out of the win column. Kendrick Perry added 12 points and six assists and Devonte Maymon had 12 points for Youngstown State. The Penguins trailed 34-33 at halftime after shooting 38.7 percent (12 of 31). However, they then made 11 of 22 from the field (50 percent), including 4 of 7 (57.1 percent) from 3-point range, to outscore Toledo 40-33 in the second half. Youngstown State trailed 54-53 with 9:41 to play, before scoring the next 13 unanswered. Eargle's three-point play put the Penguins ahead 65-54 with 5:50 to go. Malcolm Griffin had 18 points, Delino Dear 11 and Anthony Wright 10 for Toledo.
